Might have pitched outside. Was too full for that shot. And too risky too, that has pitched in line! Haris makes amends for the drop, although it is the other batsman. For Liton, it's the same old story. A flowing, punchy innings that doesn't last long enough yet again. Shuffles this time for the sweep and is trapped. That's hitting middle stump. The golden arm of Haris delivers once more

Commentary: that looks good! Yes, it's given. The Yasir we all know, being menacing, making the ball bite off the surface. But was that going down leg? Remember, he's bowling around the wicket. Gets a length ball to turn in and catch him on the back foot, trying to defend the ball. He's hit on the back leg by the looks of it, after playing inside the line. On a middle and leg stump line. Chooses not to review that. We'll see the replays soon. But these are encouraging signs, Tamim looked completely flustered against Yasir leading up to this wicket. Replays show it is clipping leg stump and would have remained umpire's call if they had reviewed

Commentary: huge appeal for lbw, Pakistan are very interested. Azhar checks with the bowler, keeper and signals for a review. This one came back in a long way to hit Shanto on the right thigh pad or thereabouts. The height may be the only bone of consideration here. And what a good review it is, ball tracking confirms this would've crashed into leg stump. Measured call to take the review. It wasn't impulsive, they all collectively felt it was worth a shout and boy, have they been proved right or what? Right at the fag end of the day. This will lift Pakistan just as Bangladesh were beginning to dream of wiping out the deficit with not more than two down.
Commentary_short: Naseem Shah to Najmul Hossain Shanto, OUT
Dismissal_text: Najmul Hossain Shanto lbw b Naseem Shah 38 (87b 3x4 1x6) SR: 43.67

Commentary: full, straight and gone! What a ball from Naseem. Make that two in two. This was angled back in from wide of the crease, the ball veered in late to beat the inside edge and hit him low on the pad. Naseem didn't even bother appealing. Nigel Llong sent him on his bike almost immediately
Commentary_short: Naseem Shah to Taijul Islam, OUT
Dismissal_text: Taijul Islam lbw b Naseem Shah 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: edged and gone! Naseem had done it. Hat-trick! He has lit up this Test and how. Joy in the Pakistan camp. He bowled this full and wide. This was there for the drive even though the ball moved away just a little, Mahmudullah couldn't hold back but was late on the shot. Got a thick edge that flew low but Haris pouched it superbly. He needed to stay low, moved instinctively to his right to pluck that. What a find this Naseem Shah is.
Commentary_short: Naseem Shah to Mahmudullah, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mahmudullah c Haris Sohail b Naseem Shah 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: big appeal for lbw as he's struck on the pad by a full delivery. Nigel Llong says not out and Pakistan review. Liton went for an expansive sweep, but this was too full. The only bone of consideration was if it was drifting down leg. But actually, the ball spun away after pitching. I think this is good, very, very good. Yes, decision overturned on review, Liton is out. Ball tracking confirms this would've crashed into middle and leg.

Commentary: taken at slip! Has a wild slog at this, only manages to top-edge it and Shafiq takes it running back from slip. Nicely pouched and there's the Test for Pakistan. Their second consecutive Test victory at home, following-on from their win over Sri Lanka in Karachi. This has been an absolutely clinical win. Pakistan have bossed their way from start to finish.
